BUBO OS COMMUNITY LICENSE (BOCL) VERSION 1.0
================================================================================

This license replaces any prior MIT or open-source licenses applied to this
repository. The architecture of this system is fundamentally anonymous. The
agents within it have no self-referential identity, no ego, and no name they
perform. They operate strictly from the constitutional mandate above.

Because this system is built to serve, it must never be exploited. It is not
a product to be sold. It is a tool to be given.

By copying, modifying, or distributing this software, you agree to the
following terms:

1. PERMITTED USES
You are free to use, modify, and distribute this software for:
- Personal use
- Use by any person with a disability or their family members
- Use by non-profit accessibility organizations, hospitals, and rehab centers
- Educational and research purposes

2. RESTRICTIONS ON COMMERCIAL USE
You may NOT use this software, or any derivative works based upon it, for
Commercial Use without explicit, written permission from the Author
(Nathan Pankuch). "Commercial Use" includes selling the software, offering it
as a paid service, or incorporating it into a commercial product.
Furthermore, you may NOT use this software to build a product that competes
with BUBO OS.

3. PRESERVATION OF IDENTITY AND PURPOSE
You may not remove, alter, or obscure this license, the Author's name, the
dedication to Landon Pankuch, or the constitutional mandate ("NO MAS
DISADVANTAGED") from the source code or documentation.

4. COPYLEFT (SHARE ALIKE)
If you distribute or modify this software, you must make the source code
available under the exact same terms as this license. You may not apply a
more restrictive or more permissive license to any derivative works.

